General Information
1. SCHEDULES & TARIFFS. Time tables and fares are subject
to change without notice.
2. RESERVATIONS. Fare must be paid immediately upon confir
mation of the fact that the seat to be reserved is available, and unless

3. STOPOVERS Stopover previleges may be arranged at the
time reservations are requested.
4. CHILDREN'S FARES. A child in arms under two years of
age and weighing not more than 10 (kilos) will be carried free when
accompanied
by
parent
or
guardian and provided parent or guardian
has paid effective fare.
A child of 2 years of age or over,
under
10 and weighing not more than 25 (kilos), may travel at half of the
standard adult fare and may occupy a seat.
5. BAGGAGE ALLOWANCE & EXCESS CHARGES 15 kilos
(33 Ibs.) of hand baggage will be carried free of charge under each full
fare ticker.
Baggage in
excess of this free allowance will be carried
only when the capacity of the aircraft permits, and when excess charges
have been paid.
The rate of excess charges will be one percent of the
single trip fare per kilo or fraction thereof.
6. RESTRICTION ON
CAMFRAS AND FIELD-GLASSES
Cameras and field glasses carried by passengers should be handed to the
pilot at the time of embarkation on the
plane and will be returned
owners
arrival
the
destination,
or they should be
locked up in any luggage which is not wanted during the trip.
7. ANIMALS & BIRDS Animals and birds will not be carried
by air.
8. POSTPONEMENT OF PASSAGE Notice of postponement
of passage
must be
given to the
Company not later
than 24 hours
immediately prior to the scheduled commencement of the initial flight
of anv

will
be endorsed
accordingly,
provided there is
seat accommodation available on the date to which
the passage is postponed.

10. MEATS The Corporation provides no meals for passengers.
11. CANCELLATION OF TICKET BY THE CORPORATION
The corporation reserves the right to cancel any ticket at any
time
for emergency reasons without previous notice.
12. RITES & REGULATIONS Passengers must comply with
the rules and regulations of the Corporation.
These rules and regula-
tions are provided separately.
